cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on computer vision applications such as scene understanding and plane segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes clustering algorithms, which are commonly studied in machine learning and statistics, falling under cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of surface normals in 3D reconstructions suggests a connection to computer graphics, which is often categorized under cs.CL. Finally, the mention of high dimensional directional data such as protein backbone configurations and semantic word vectors suggests a connection to neural networks and natural language processing, which are often categorized under cs.NE and cs.CL, respectively.
